name: Nick Maag
text: Very good deep dish pizza.  The garlic thing like other guy said was ok but tastes just like crazy bread but in they are in bites.  Be warned of you are picking up deep dish for home because it can leak with the gold holes in their box.  My picture is of the delicious deep dish and the leak.

name: Lora Gauthier
text: Tried the deep dish cheese. Sauce tasted great but this was the weirdest "Chicago style" pizza I've ever had. It was like shredded mozzarella was mixed into the sauce instead of a separate layer UNDER the sauce. Crust was pretty good. All the flavors were there, just a complete miss texture wise. I don't get it.

name: Drew Sutton
text: Top notch pizza! We love bringing the kids on Monday and Tuesday since kids eat free. The chopped salad in yum!  My husband loves the deep dish pizza. Fresh ingredients

name: Gregor J. Rothfuss
text: Decent takeout pies.

name: donald weitzman
text: The BEST pizza and wings we have EVER had!!! Food came hot and quickly with the portions being WAY bigger than we expected. Definitely worth the money and we will get this pizza any time we are in the Frisco area.  Crossing my fingers they open one in Austin!!!

name: Scott Brooks
text: The worst pizza experience I've ever had.  Tried to order online and the coupons they had sent in the mail did not work.  There were absolutely no parking spots when I got there at 5:15 for pick up (Custer and Eldorado).  Most places that ‚Ä¶More

name: Jordan Edwards
text: First off I want to say and acknowledge how well the staff handles customer service!  Ran into a situation where one of my orders came to me unsatisfactory.  Having the issue resolved by Tasha from the Mckinney location, and Ray from the ‚Ä¶More

name: Keita Allison
text: Worked there. God awful. Absolutely do not recommend.  And knowing what all happens in the kitchen makes me terrified that people actually eat this food. No sanitation what so ever. Roaches everywhere. Even IN THE FOOD.

name: Sean Green
text: I have tried the thin crust pizza, wings, hot beef sandwich, pasta, and salads. Every meal from this place has been great. I'm a fan.

name: Brandon Young
text: Good pizza until they tried to charge me $19 for a kids pizza they all lost in the sauce at this place. When he said $19 for a kids pizza it instantly became nasty üòë

name: Brooklynn R.
text: Im from Chicago and I had this pizza today in Lewisville for a work related meeting. Without paying attention to the name I ate and at first bite tasted a bit of home. I googled a location that's luckily near where I actually live and will be ordering dinner for the family. Tonight I'll try the deep dish.

name: Daniel Thomas
text: Had The Works on deep dish crust, absolutely fantastic. The cheese garlic bread...not so much, fairly disappointing. However the pizza is top notch and loaded with toppings.

name: James Casmay
text: I'm from Chicago and we do not eat burnt pizza.  While visiting town, I decided to get a taste of home.  Little did I know the pizza would arrive burnt via delivery driver.

name: Suhail Hirani
text: The best pizza in town!! Excellent food. Taste of Chicago!

name: Firefly
text: I'm from Chicago so I had high exceptions.  The beef is dry and skimpy.  Everything is overpriced.  The sausage is usually overcooked.  Delivery takes FOREVER even though we only order sandwiches.  We have ordered several times to try to ‚Ä¶More

name: Joy Lawrence
text: For this Chicagoian who has been transferred down to McKinney I was elated to send a favorite eatery of ours. Unfortunately we ordered the cheesy beef which had no flavor and was very dry. The Italian beef was just the same.  This is not the place for true Italian beef sandwiches. .for shame.

name: Matthias A
text: Deep dish pizza had decent flavor. Not worth $30 for a 12 inch pizza though.
